<br>
Bank System and Looting Policy for Raids:<br>
&gt;NBG on Raids.<br>
&gt;When an item drops and is linked, respond in a tell to the Raid Leader with a link to the item you wish to upgrade...<br>
&gt;A new thing we're going to be trying out: If the item you are upgrading is droppable, then you will turn it in to the guild bank so that it may be passed on to someone else's MAIN (this will hopefully trickle down upgrades to everyone within the guild)... If the item is NO DROP then you keep the item (we're not expecting the impossible here <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  ).<br>
&gt;The other prong of this experiment is: If you recieve an item from the guild bank, then you will turn in the item that is upgraded, UNLESS it is NO DROP.<br>
&gt;There will be a time requirement of 1 month and 3 raids in order for new recruits to recieve equipment from the guild bank.<br>
&gt;Proceeds from any guild bank sales will go towards Spells, Reagents, and other do-dads.<br>
&gt;In the future we hope to be moving to a DKP (Dragon Kill Points) System, in which on a raid you will earn points per named mob you help to kill.<br>
<br>
Posting Raids:<br>
&gt;Anyone can now post and lead a raid... if you wish to post a raid but not lead it contact an officer or fellow guildy about leading the raid for you.<br>
&gt;Guidelines for what you need to post when planning a raid will be posted shortly.<br>
<br>
Webpage:<br>
&gt;Faelawen will be taking over the updates on the webpage shortly (as soon as he learns how to do it).<br>
&gt;In the future, Cypres and Nnyx will also be brought into the team to help keep the site as updated as possible.<br>
<br>
PL Session:<br>
&gt;Soon to come in the raid section will be posts offering PL sessions... in order to recieve one of these sessions you must be one of the first to post in the tread that you want to use it... so watch closely 'cause if only one person is checking the site then they'll be the only one getting xp sessions personalized for them...<br>
&gt;We'll also be setting up first teir and second teir groups for higher level toons <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Alt Tags:<br>
&gt;We're going to start publicly posting who everyone's alt is... if you look in the guild management tool you will see several people have already done this.  In order to be tagged, send a tell to an officer and request that they post your alt tags.<br>
&gt;NOTE TO OFFICERS: If you invite someone's alt into the guild, then automatically tag them at that time.<br>
<br>
Language in Guild Chat:<br>
&gt;In response to some concerns that have been expressed due to the age appropriateness of language in guild chat, we have started up a chat channel specifically for adult language... this includes explatives and vulgar language (in other words, things mothers wouldn't want to see on their young people's monitors).  This channel IS password protected, please ask for the channel name and password IN GAME.<br>
<br>
Hopefully these new changes will make eveyone's gaming experience more joyful. Hope to see you all soon.<br>
Tsiah<br>
